    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aGuideHub!  To change background color of mui badge in react js, you can use this code . This will change background color of mui‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aGuideHub! </p>\n<p>To change background color of mui badge in react js, you can use this code <code class=\"language-text\">color=\"success\"</code>. This will change background color of mui badge in React JS.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to change background color of mui badge in react js.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Install the following packages to use mui Badge in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">npm</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npm install @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">yarn</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">yarn add @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install MUI and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import Material-UI Badge.</li>\n<li>Use the Badge Component</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Step 1: Install MUI and create a new React app.</h3>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Import Material-UI Badge.</h3>\n<p>After installing <code class=\"language-text\">MUI</code>, you have to import your React component. To do this, add the following line to the top of your component file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> Badge <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@mui/material'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 3: Use the Badge Component.</h3>\n<p>You can use the <code class=\"language-text\">Badge</code> component in your react js. For example, The Badge component is used to notification. You can use <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Badge></code> component make a Badge box in react js.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Badge badgeContent<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> color<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"success\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token comment\">/* Content */</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Badge<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>MUI material change background color of mui badge example.</h2>\n<p>The below code is an example, you need to import <code class=\"language-text\">Badge</code> Component. you can use this code <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Badge badgeContent={10} color=\"success\"></code> and to change background color of mui badge in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> Badge <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@mui/material'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">App</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Badge badgeContent<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> color<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"success\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token comment\">/* Content */</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Badge<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">@mui/material</code> component and changed background color of mui badge in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code example.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 283px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/5e4063166918777d66c43d334316400b/30314/background-bedge.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 44.30379746835443%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRloAAABXRUJQVlA4IE4AAABwAwCdASoUAAkAPtFUo0uoJKMhsAgBABoJQBOgBDwp5E70dyAA/Z166ubzmWaOPsqAnEzRlQhKejQ2FmQBzHxgNxCYKZV1RWEthLIhSAA='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, Mui, background, bedge\"\n        title=\"React, Mui, background, bedge\"\n        src=\"/static/5e4063166918777d66c43d334316400b/30314/background-bedge.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5e4063166918777d66c43d334316400b/81b7c/background-bedge.webp 158w,\n/static/5e4063166918777d66c43d334316400b/30314/background-bedge.webp 283w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 283px) 100vw, 283px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Here, we are provided code sandbox links for the above program change background color of mui badge in react js. Then you can use whenever you want and do the changes as per your requirements.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://aguidehub.com/codesandbox/?code=eager-kate-8kxf9t\" rel=\"nofollow\"  target=\"_BLANK\" >Try it Yourself</a></p>\n<p>All the best üëç</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to change background color of mui badge in react js?","tags":["React"],"date":"June 27, 2023","description":"Example of change background color of mui badge in React js with step by step tutorial - aGuideHub","social_image":"media/template/reactjs.jpg"}},"prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to show mui alert without icon in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2023-06-27-how-to-show-mui-alert-without-icon-in-react-js/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to show mui alert as toast in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2023-06-26-how-to-show-mui-alert-as-toast-in-react-js/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/2023-06-27-how-to-change-background-color-of-mui-badge-in-react-js/","prevSlug":"/blog/2023-06-27-how-to-show-mui-alert-without-icon-in-react-js/","nextSlug":"/blog/2023-06-26-how-to-show-mui-alert-as-toast-in-react-js/"}},
